via VIASA...World's First All-Jet Airline
VIASA INTERNATIONAL AIRWAYS ...
serves the United States through
three gateways: New York, Miami and New Orleans.
Principal destinations in Venezuela are Caracas' airport at
Maiquetia and oil-rich Maracaibo, with flights continuing
to Bogota, Colombia and Lima, Peru. Other flights
touch down at Panama, Santo Domingo non-stop from
New York, and other Caribbean and South American points.
GOURMET DINING SEVEN MILES HIGH!
Select meals from menus printed in three languages
... enjoy truly hospitable service. Each course is served
from a rolling cart with appropriate vintage wine.
After-dinner liqueurs grace your adventure in dining,
just before your Viasa jet glides smoothly to
the airport of your destination.
COCKTAIL BEFORE DINNER?
Yours for the asking! Made from choice
whiskies, gins and scotch liquors from the
world's nnest brands. brandy, too, and bourbon.
AND, of course, french champagne. Just a request to
the steward and the liquor cart comes to your seat,
where your drink is mixed to your preterence. anouter
luxury note on the World's First All-Jet Airline.
VENEZUELA.
exotic land of orchids, diamonds and pearls. Spectacular
scenery and 3,212-foot Angel Falls. Big-game
hunting and fantastic fishing. Lush tropical jungles in
the "Lost World" and skiing in the Andes. Crumbling
Spanish forts slumbering in the sun. Called
"paradise" by Christopher Columbus in 1498.
